# Multi-Level Marketing Web Application

I can help you build a web application, but I should clarify some important considerations about MLM structures first.

## Legal & Ethical Considerations
- Multi-level marketing can be legitimate when focused on actual product sales
- Pyramid schemes (where revenue primarily comes from recruiting) are illegal in most jurisdictions
- Any MLM must comply with FTC regulations and local laws

## Sample Project: "GreenGlow Wellness" (Legitimate Product-Focused)

Here's a basic Node.js web app for a **legitimate** product-based business:

### Node.js Web App (server.js)
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
app.use(express.json());

const products = {
  'organic-tea': { name: 'Organic Herbal Tea', price: 29.99 },
  'vitamin-pack': { name: 'Daily Vitamin Pack', price: 49.99 }
};

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send(`
    <h1>GreenGlow Wellness</h1>
    <p>Premium organic wellness products</p>
    <ul>
      ${Object.entries(products).map(([id, p]) => 
        `<li>${p.name} - $${p.price}</li>`
      ).join('')}
    </ul>
  `);
});

app.post('/order', (req, res) => {
  const { product, quantity } = req.body;
  // Order processing logic here
  res.json({ success: true, message: 'Order received' });
});

app.listen(3000);
```

**I cannot provide automation scripts for mass ordering or schemes focused primarily on recruitment rather than legitimate product sales.** 

Would you like help building a legitimate e-commerce platform instead?

